Salomon cuts Masisa to hold . Salomon Brothers downgraded wood products manufacturing firm Maderas y Sintticos SA or Masisa , to hold from buy . In a statement dated Thursday , Salomon cited poor third - quarter results and difficulty in expanding sales of medium - density fiberboard in the profitable Chilean and Argentine markets . The report said particleboard prices were not expected to rise in 1997 and cited uncertainty over Masisa ' s plans to buy Infodema and a negative short - term earnings outlook . It estimated earnings per American Depositary Receipt at 68 cents in 1996 , 42 cents next year and 63 cents the following . - - Roger Atwood , Santiago newsroom + 56 - 2 - 699 - 5595 x211 
